auvoir’s writings and film studies. The authors analyse a range of films, from directors including Claire Denis, Michael Haneke, Lucille Hadzihalilovic, Sam Mendes, and Sally Potter, by drawing from Beauvoir’s key works such as The Second Sex (1949), The Ethics of Ambiguity (1947) and Old Age (1970).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aExistentialism in motion pictures. 0aFeminism and motion pictures. 0aPhilosophy in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aBainbrigge, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoulé, Jean-Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoulé, Jean-Pierre, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDavis, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHumphrey, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInce, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMui, Constance, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMurphy, Julien, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoyer, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSecomb, Linnell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStephens, Bradley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTidd, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTidd, Ursula, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWilson, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745730140uhttps://www.degru